Standard Bank Group said first-half profit rose 4% as higher income from its operations outside of South Africa helped compensate for slower economic growth in its home market. Net income in the six months through June climbed to R13.2 billion, the Johannesburg-based lender said in a statement. Its credit-loss ratio deteriorated to 0.76% from 0.62% a year earlier. Key insights Read: Standard Bank branch cuts are long overdue Standard Bank AGM a ‘watershed’ © 2019 Bloomberg L.P.